snippet.title: Squid Game: Season 2 | Official Teaser | Netflix
snippet.description:
There's no stopping the game.

Squid Game Season 2 on December 26, 2024.

Only on Netflix.

More Info on Squid Game Season 2:
Three years after winning Squid Game, Player 456 gave up going to the states and comes back with a new resolution in his mind. Gi-hun once again dives into the mysterious survival game, starting another life-or-death game with new participants gathered to win the prize of 45.6 billion won.

Director Hwang Dong-hyuk, who made history at the 74th Primetime Emmys¬Æ becoming the first Asian to win Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series, once again helms the series as director, writer, and producer. Lee Jung-jae, Lee Byung-hun, Wi Ha-jun, and Gong Yoo reprise their roles from Season 1 with an impeccable list of new cast members including Yim Si-wan, Kang Ha-neul, Park Gyu-young, Lee Jin-uk, Park Sung-hoon, Yang Dong-geun, Kang Ae-sim, Lee David, Choi Seung-hyun, Roh Jae-won, Jo Yu-ri, and Won Ji-an rounding out the ensemble of colorful characters in the new season.

Watch on Netflix: https://www.netflix.com/title/81203480

About Netflix:
Netflix is one of the world's leading entertainment services, with 283 million paid memberships in over 190 countries enjoying TV series, films and games across a wide variety of genres and languages. Members can play, pause and resume watching as much as they want, anytime, anywhere, and can change their plans at any time.

Squid Game: Season 2 | Official Teaser | Netflix
https://www.youtube.com/@Netflix

Heralding the return of the worldwide hit, a new chapter unfolds as Gi-hun comes back with an agenda, having given up on leaving for the US.

Episode 4232: Sarees For Mahila Mandal
--------------------------------------------------------
Champaklal invites the Mahila Mandal to his house and gifts them sarees for Diwali. Meanwhile, the men of Gokuldham gather at Abdul's shop. Later, Bhide announces that free firecrackers will be given to all society members.

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.title: Indians And Diwali | Ft. Tena Jaiin | The Paayal Jain
snippet.description:
Hey Guys
Happy Diwali to all of you , may this diwali brings joy , laughter , prosperity 

As the Title is Indians And Diwali this Video has everything that happens during Diwali Festival . The most relatable and Funny Diwali Video . Scenarios like what happens on Indian families doing Diwali shopping for dhanteras shopping new utensils or jewellery shopping of gold coin , silver coin from brand like Tanishq . Kaamwali and her struggles with house cleaning waiting for diwali gifts , diwali bonus . Daughter painting diya and mom hanging diwali lights . Girls dressing up in traditional dieting whole month to look good and clicking pictures and making videos . Preparations for office diwali pooja , sisters cleaning house and competing and having fun , next day of diwali and taking off the lights , flower garlands , rangoli , giving diwali to staff , guards , kaamwali bai , Aunties for shopping for diwali pooja kheel patashe , patisha , paan , supari , sweets , favourite mathai moti choor ladoo , kaju ki barfi , bondi ke laddoo , cham cham , diwali decoration , bhandan var , diya , lights , candles , rangoli , diwali gifts dry fruits , gift box . Indian Aunties bargaining with shopkeeper , shops making huge profits during diwali dhamaka sales , going out to relatives to wish happy diwali and dealing with diwali 2024 traffic jams , giving gifts to relatives and travelling in car , indian sweets shops fully loaded with customers , eating in restaurants after diwali shopping , shopkeeper selling bandhanbar , latkane , diwali decorations , eating dosa , chowmein , work from home people busy with job and ghar ki safai , tuition mam helps kids prepare their diwali poem , diwali essay , teaching why diwali is celebrated , diwali school function costumes , diwali is the festival food , every foodie loves puri , mathi , samosa , ladoo , aloo , kheer , halwa , muli ki bhujji , raita , achar , panchamrit , laxmi ganesh pooja , house aura cleansing with diwali aarti , talking about the ban on fire crackers , diwali away from home , pg wali diwali , showing off chandi , gold gifts , buying air purifier cause of the air pollution and noise pullution caused by crackers in delhi , south delhi posh diwali partiers playing poker , drinking , tambola , diwali vlogs , diwali outfits , lehenga , suits , saree , kurti , kurta , and looking beautiful and clicking pictures . West Delhi people mocking south delhi on dieting on diwali doing keto , intermittent fasting or just drinking alcohol , many more fun things covered in the diwali video .
This video is filled with Festive season memories and situations we all have been in . 
Relish and Relive your Childhood Memories of Diwali festival
Do share it with your friends and family , Relatives , Neighbour . A very happy diwali 2024 season to all of you and Happy deepawali  .. Comment down your Fav Part , 
Like , Share and

Hey Guys
Happy Diwali to all of you , may this diwali brings joy , laughter , prosperity 

As the Title is Indians And Diwali this Video has everything that happens during Diwali Festival . The most relatable and Funny Diwali Video . Scenarios like what happens on Indian families doing Diwali shopping for dhanteras shopping new utensils or jewellery shopping of gold coin , silver coin from brand like Tanishq . Kaamwali and her struggles with house cleaning waiting for diwali gifts , diwali bonus . Daughter painting diya and mom hanging diwali lights . Girls dressing up in traditional dieting whole month to look good and clicking pictures and making videos . Preparations for office diwali pooja , sisters cleaning house and competing and having fun , next day of diwali and taking off the lights , flower garlands , rangoli , giving diwali to staff , guards , kaamwali bai , Aunties for shopping for diwali pooja kheel patashe , patisha , paan , supari , sweets , favourite mathai moti choor ladoo , kaju ki barfi , bondi ke laddoo , cham cham , diwali decoration , bhandan var , diya , lights , candles , rangoli , diwali gifts dry fruits , gift box . Indian Aunties bargaining with shopkeeper , shops making huge profits during diwali dhamaka sales , going out to relatives to wish happy diwali and dealing with diwali 2024 traffic jams , giving gifts to relatives and travelling in car , indian sweets shops fully loaded with customers , eating in restaurants after diwali shopping , shopkeeper selling bandhanbar , latkane , diwali decorations , eating dosa , chowmein , work from home people busy with job and ghar ki safai , tuition mam helps kids prepare their diwali poem , diwali essay , teaching why diwali is celebrated , diwali school function costumes , diwali is the festival food , every foodie loves puri , mathi , samosa , ladoo , aloo , kheer , halwa , muli ki bhujji , raita , achar , panchamrit , laxmi ganesh pooja , house aura cleansing with diwali aarti , talking about the ban on fire crackers , diwali away from home , pg wali diwali , showing off chandi , gold gifts , buying air purifier cause of the air pollution and noise pullution caused by crackers in delhi , south delhi posh diwali partiers playing poker , drinking , tambola , diwali vlogs , diwali outfits , lehenga , suits , saree , kurti , kurta , and looking beautiful and clicking pictures . West Delhi people mocking south delhi on dieting on diwali doing keto , intermittent fasting or just drinking alcohol , many more fun things covered in the diwali video .
This video is filled with Festive season memories and situations we all have been in . 
Relish and Relive your Childhood Memories of Diwali festival

Special Occasions and Deities:

* Guru Tamil Devotional Songs: Songs to honor Guru and seek his wisdom.
* Perumal Tamil Devotional Songs: Devote to Lord Perumal with these spiritual songs.
* Navagraha Tamil Devotional Songs: Balance your energies with songs for the nine planets.

IPL 2025 Retentions: Full list of retained and released players by all 10 franchises ahead of mega auction.
The road to the 2025 IPL season is well underway, as the ten franchises announced their retention lists ahead of the big auction set to occur before the close of the year. In an IPL Retention Special on JioCinema, the teams announced which players will continue to represent their jerseys in the tournament next year ‚Äî but also some big names who will be going under the hammer in the auction, who teams will keep an eye on.
Heinrich Klaasen was the highest earner in the retention lists, with Sunrisers Hyderabad giving him 23 crore to keep his services. Virat Kohli and Nicholas Pooran were right behind, as RCB and LSG give them INR 21 cr each.
On the other hands, some big-name players will be seeking new homes in the auction. Amongst these are Delhi franchise hero Rishabh Pant who was confirmed as released in a shock move, as well as KL Rahul, KKR title-winning captain Shreyas Iyer, and a premium Indian fast bowler in the form of Arshdeep Singh as well. They are joined by some big-name overseas players as well, headed by Jos Buttler and Glenn Maxwell.
Punjab Kings retained the fewest players, and Ricky Ponting will have a warchest of 110.5 cr in the auction, by far the most in this year‚Äôs auction. RCB will also have 83 crore on hand with only three retentions, while DC will have 73 cr under their new leadership as well. KKR and RR will both head into the auction with the maximum of six players already in their squads, but the Jaipur team will have only 41 cr to work with at the auction, with no RTM possibilities either.
Here's the full list of retained and released players by all 10 IPL franchises ahead of mega auction

The road to the 2025 IPL season is well underway, as the ten franchises announced their retention lists ahead of the big auction set to occur before the close of the year. In an IPL Retention Special on JioCinema, the teams announced which players will continue to represent their jerseys in the tournament next year ‚Äî but also some big names who will be going under the hammer in the auction, who teams will keep an eye on.
Heinrich Klaasen was the highest earner in the retention lists, with Sunrisers Hyderabad giving him 23 crore to keep his services. Virat Kohli and Nicholas Pooran were right behind, as RCB and LSG give them INR 21 cr each.
On the other hands, some big-name players will be seeking new homes in the auction. Amongst these are Delhi franchise hero Rishabh Pant who was confirmed as released in a shock move, as well as KL Rahul, KKR title-winning captain Shreyas Iyer, and a premium Indian fast bowler in the form of Arshdeep Singh as well. They are joined by some big-name overseas players as well, headed by Jos Buttler and Glenn Maxwell.
Punjab Kings retained the fewest players, and Ricky Ponting will have a warchest of 110.5 cr in the auction, by far the most in this year‚Äôs auction. RCB will also have 83 crore on hand with only three retentions, while DC will have 73 cr under their new leadership as well. KKR and RR will both head into the auction with the maximum of six players already in their squads, but the Jaipur team will have only 41 cr to work with at the auction, with no RTM possibilities either.

snippet.title: MIXTURE Snack | DIWALI Special Traditional Mixture Recipe Cooking In Village | South Indian Snacks
snippet.description:
Mixture Recipe is a popular snack recipe in South India, especially in Tamil Nadu, Kerala and Karnataka. Today, we are cooking this recipe as a Diwali Special. The specialty of this snack is its mixed taste. 

To enhance the flavor of this mixture, we use Boondi, Fried Nuts, Fried Spices, and other healthy ingredients, along with Omappodi.

The taste is memorable!

IPL 2025 retention: List of players retained and released by each team.

Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli and MS Dhoni were the big names to be retained by their respective teams while Rishabh Pant, KL Rahul and Shreyas Iyer were released.
The list of retained and released players by each team ahead of the Indian Premier League 2025 mega auction included plenty of surprises on Thursday.

While big names like Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, MS Dhoni, Pat Cummins, Heinrich Klaasen and Nicholas Pooran were retained by their respective teams, Rishabh Pant, Shreyas Iyer, Mitchell Starc and KL Rahul were released ahead of the mega auction.

All 10 cricket teams executed their IPL 2025 retention strategies to maintain a balanced core. Each team could retain up to five capped players, two uncapped players, and a maximum of six players in total.

Teams that retained fewer players will have more Right-to-Match (RTM) options and a larger purse going into the mega auction later this year.


Punjab Kings retained two uncapped players - Shashank Singh and Prabhsimran Singh - and none in the capped category. At the mega auction, they will have four RTM options available for capped players.

Five-time champions Mumbai Indians went for a contrasting approach, retaining five capped players - Rohit Sharma, Suryakumar Yadav, Hardik Pandya, Jasprit Bumrah and Tilak Varma - and none in the uncapped category.

Defending champions Kolkata Knight Riders released their title-winning captain Shreyas Iyer but used all six of their retentions to keep mystery spinner Sunil Narine, Varun Chakravarthy, Rinku Singh, Andre Russell, Ramandeep Singh and Harshit Rana in the team. Rajasthan Royals also used up all six of their retentions.

Like the Kolkata Knight Riders, Delhi Capitals, Lucknow Super Giants, Punjab Kings and Royal Challlenger Bengaluru also let go of their captains from the previous season with Rishabh Pant, KL Rahul, Sam Curran and Faf du Plessis set to enter the mega auction.

The Chennai Super Kings retained former Indian captain MS Dhoni under the uncapped player category. Per the IPL retention rules, players who did not play international cricket in the last five years came under the uncapped category
